# Vehicle Management System (Java Program)

A simple Java OOP-based program that demonstrates the creation of a **Vehicle class** with constructors, getters/setters, and basic operational methods.
The application creates multiple vehicle objects, stores them in an array, and displays vehicle details in **tabular format** with basic validation cases.

## Features

* Default, parameterized, and copy constructors
* Encapsulation using private data members with getters/setters
* Methods: start(), stop(), drive(), calcMileage(), changeSpeed()
* Multiple vehicle object creation and array handling
* Tabular display of Brand, Model, Price, Mileage, Mfg Code, and Efficiency
* Basic error handling for invalid price, zero fuel, and missing details

## Technologies Used

* Java (JDK 8 or above)
* VS Code / Any Java IDE
* Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts
* Command-line execution

